class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n < 1) {
            return false;
        }
        double log = Math.log(n) / Math.log(3);
        return Math.floor(log) == log;
    }
}
```

In this solution, we first check if the input `n` is less than 1. If it is, we return `false` because negative numbers and 0 are not powers of three.

Then, we calculate the logarithm of `n` with base 3 using `Math.log(n) / Math.log(3)`. This gives us the exponent `x` such that `n == 3^x`.

Finally, we check if the exponent `x` is an integer by comparing it with its floor value using `Math.floor(log) == log`. If they are equal, it means `x` is an integer, so `n` is a power of three, and we return `true`. Otherwise, we return `false`.

